.TH "try_charger_enable" 9 "try_charger_enable" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
try_charger_enable \- Enable/Disable chargers altogether
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" try_charger_enable
.BI "(struct charger_manager *cm "  ","
.BI "bool enable "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cm" 12
the Charger Manager representing the battery.
.IP "enable" 12
true: enable / false: disable
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Note that Charger Manager keeps the charger enabled regardless whether
the charger is charging or not (because battery is full or no external
power source exists) except when CM needs to disable chargers forcibly
because of emergency causes; when the battery is overheated or too cold.
